A 52-year-old man was killed and a 53-year-old woman was seriously injured when a driver hit them while they were crossing the road near 90th Street and 62nd Avenue in St. Petersburg on Saturday night. According to St. Petersburg police, a 24-year-old driver in a sedan was heading eastbound on 62nd when two pedestrians, Sean Lewis and Michelle Lewis, were crossing the street mid-block. Police said the driver struck the two pedestrians while they were in the south curb lane, and not at a crosswalk, around 10:30 p.m. Sean Lewis was pronounced dead at the scene, and Michelle Lewis was taken to Bayfront Health St. Petersburg with serious injuries. She is now in stable condition, police said. No charges have been filed. Police said an investigation is ongoing. This is a developing story. Stay with tampabay.com for updates.